comments.content: Lots of House Industries IDs recently...

GASKET GOONS 77  
DID ANYONE HERE GO TO THE PARTY IN JULY

THIS IS THE LOGO FOR A CAR & MOTORCYCLE CLUB ON THE EAST COAST.GASKET GOONS,PARTS UNKNOWN,IS A CLUB THAT FOUR VERY DEAR FRIENDS CAME UP WITH ON A ROAD TRIP TO THE WEST COAST.I KNOW THIS BECAUSE I AM ONE OF THE FOUNDING FATHERS.NOW,DOES ANYONE KNOW WHAT THE 77 STANDS FOR? IF YOU THINK YOU KNOW,THEN PLEASE REPLY.I WILL KNOW BY YOUR REPLY IF YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE TALKING ABOUT!

John, could you please stop typing in all caps? In basic internet etiquette, this means you are shouting.

Also, although some people here may have heard of this motorcycle club, this thread was for the ID of the typefaces in their logo. Your questions are better suited to the General Discussions board.

- Lex
the 7 & 7 stands for the 7th letter of the alphabet (G) the 77 represents the word Gasket Goons.
